INTRODUCTION
This Document is the Work Instruction (WI) for Employee Training
PURPOSE
This WI defines the steps that are followed to implement and monitor Employee
Training in the organisation
SCOPE
The WI applies to the QMSrs Tool set that accompanies this WI

EMPLOYEE TRAINING PROCESS
This section displays the flow of the process.
EMPLOYEE TRAINING WORK INSTRUCTION
ADMIN MENU
This menu can by used by the administrator- coordinator or instructor to administrate the
module, it include the following:
CREATE COURSE
This section explains how to create a course in the QMS.
To create a course:
 Go to Employee Training section in the QMS.
 From Admin Menu select ‘Create Course’.
 Fill the mandatory fields with the red asterisk ‘*’ and any other fields you
have data for.
 Click on save icon “ ” to save changes that appears at the top of the
window.

MANAGE COURSES
Course Details
Course ID
Enter the ID of the course
Course Title
Enter the course title
Description
Enter the course description
Start Date
Select the course date from the calendar
Duration
Enter the duration time and select the value from drop
down list in terms of (days, years, months) for the course
End date
Select the course end date from the calendar
Course Capacity
Enter the maximum number of employee who can attend
the course
Course Coordinator
Click on search sign" " and select the name of the
employee who will coordinate the course from the drop
down list
Course Material
Click on search sign" " and select the name of the
document type
Accommodation
Check the box for the available accommodation for this
course ( refreshment-lunch and transportation)

This section displays the courses schedule. Click on course title to view the course

User can edit a course (if the course is not completed or cancelled) or delete it.
EDIT A COURSE
 Go to Employee Training section in the QMS.
 From Admin Menu select ‘Manage Courses’.
 Click on the title of the course that you want to edit.
 Click on edit icon“ “that appears at the end of the window.
 Make the necessary changes.
 Click on “Save “to save the amended data or “Cancel” to cancel the changes.
DELETE A COURSE
 Go to Employee Training section in the QMS.
 From Admin Menu select ‘Manage Courses’.
 Click on the title of the course that you want to delete.
 Click on delete icon “ “beside the course that you want to delete.
 To delete the course click on “OK “or “Cancel “to cancel deleting.

MANAGE COURSE SCHEDUALE

To add a session:
 Go to Employee Training section in the QMS.
 From Admin Menu select ‘Manage Course schedule’.
 Click on search sign" " then select the course that you want to add session
for from the drop down list.
 Click on add icon " “.
 Fill the mandatory fields with the red asterisk ‘*’ and any other fields you
have data for.
 Click on “Save “to save the amended data or “Cancel” to cancel the changes.

EDIT A SESSION
Course Session Details
Session Date
Select the date from the calendar
Beginning Time
Enter the start time of the course in HH:MM format
Ending Time
Enter the end time of the course in HH: MM format
Instructor Type
Select the type of the instructor from the drop down list
(Employee, external...)
Select Instructor
Click on search sign" " then select the Instructor from
the drop down list .Instructors will appear in the list
according to their type
(Employee  choose his/her unit then select his/her
name)
(External  choose his/her type (corporation,
individual…) then select his/her name)
Select venue
Select the location where the course will be held from
the drop down list
User can add a new location by clicking on add sign" "
then enter the details of the location (name, address,
country, city, website…

 Click on search sign" " then select the course that you want to enrol a
course for from the drop down list.
 Click on add icon " “.
 Fill the mandatory fields with the red asterisk ‘*’ and any other fields you
have data for.
 Click on “Save “to save the amended data or “Cancel” to cancel the changes.

REPORTS
LIST OF COURSES
In this section user can display all the courses with their status (Created,
Scheduled…).
Different filter criteria can be used (Status, Record Mode, Start Date …).
User can use varying criteria as follows:
 Click on filter icon “ “at the top of the window, then choose the search
criteria you want.
 Select from the drop down list and click on next icon" ".
 To clear the result of filtration click on delete Filter icon" ".
In this dynamic report, the user can choose the fields that he wants to appear in the
chart by selecting from the drop down list of “display fields” that found at the top of
the page and then click on “ “ icon.

COURSE ATTENDANCE LIST
In this section user can display the completed courses with their attendance status
(Attended, Absent, Undermined…).
User can search specific course by entering its name in the course title field and click
on next icon" ".
In this dynamic report, the user can choose the fields that he wants to appear in the
chart by selecting from the drop down list of “display fields” that found at the top of
the page and then click on “ “ icon.
COURSE FEEDBACK LIST
In this section user can display feedback status of any completed course after
selecting it from the drop down list, the chart will illustrate the percentage of
attendees who provided Feedback and who didn’t provided Feedback.
In this dynamic report, the user can choose the fields that he wants to appear in the
chart by selecting from the drop down list of “display fields” that found at the top of
the page and then click on “ “ icon.
STATICSTIC OF HELD COURSES
In this section user can display all the held and not held courses.
User can use the filter to select the year from the drop down list.
In this dynamic report, the user can choose the fields that he wants to appear in the
chart by selecting from the drop down list of “display fields” that found at the top of
the page and then click on “ “ icon.

USER MENU
In this section the user can view a course, withdrew from a course or apply for feedback.
VIEW COURSES
ADD FEEDBACK
 Go to Employee Training section in the QMS.
 From User Menu select ‘View Courses’.
 The user can add feedback for all the courses that he/she attended and the
status of them is completed
 Click on add feedback icon" "
 Answer all the question
 Click on “Save “to save the amended data or “Cancel” to cancel the changes.
